'''BoardGameGeek'''（简称'''BGG'''，意思為「棋盤遊戲極客」或「桌遊極客」）是为[[棋盘游戏|棋盘游戏]]爱好者服务的在线论坛和游戏数据库，其中包含超过125,600种不同[[桌上游戏|桌面游戏]]的评论、图像和视频，包括[[德式桌上游戏|欧式棋盘游戏]]、[[战争游戏|战争游戏]]和[[卡牌游戏|卡牌游戏]]<ref name="Eurogames">{{cite book |title=Eurogames: The Design, Culture and Play of Modern European Board Games |last=Woods |first=Stewart |publisher=[[McFarland_&_Company|McFarland]] |year=2009 |isbn=0786467975}}</ref>。除游戏数据库外，该网站还允许用户对游戏进行1分-10分的评价，并发布棋盘游戏排名列表<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.dailydot.com/parsec/best-family-board-games/ |title=The 10 best board games for families |last=Riese |first=Monica |date=2016-09-25 |newspaper=The Daily Dot |access-date=2016-11-10 |archive-date=2019-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190526142046/https://www.dailydot.com/parsec/best-family-board-games/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://fivethirtyeight.com/features/stop-playing-monopoly-with-your-kids-and-play-these-games-instead/ |title=Stop Playing Monopoly With Your Kids (And Play These Games Instead) |last=Roeder |first=Oliver |date=2015-01-22 |newspaper=FiveThirtyEight |language=en-US |access-date=2016-11-10 |archive-date=2019-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190526142047/https://fivethirtyeight.com/features/stop-playing-monopoly-with-your-kids-and-play-these-games-instead/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2016/03/pandemic-legacy-is-the-best-board-game-ever-but-is-it-fun/ |title=Pandemic Legacy is the best board game ever—but is it "fun?" |last=Anderson |first=Nate |newspaper=Ars Technica |access-date=2016-11-10 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308033415/https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2016/03/pandemic-legacy-is-the-best-board-game-ever-but-is-it-fun/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。截至2021年，《{{tsl|en|Gloomhaven|幽港迷城}}》是评分最高的游戏。

==历史==
BoardGameGeek由斯科特·奥尔登（Scott Alden）和德克·索尔科（Derk Solko）于2000年1月创立<ref name=":0">{{Cite book |title=Eurogames: The Design, Culture and Play of Modern European Board Games |last=Woods |first=Stewart |publisher=McFarland |year=2012 |isbn=9780786490653 |pages=121 |via=Google Books}}</ref>，于2020年1月20日庆祝成立20周年<ref>Damerst, Lincoln (20 January 2020). [https://boardgamegeek.com/thread/2352850 "Happy 20th Anniversary BGG! Jan 20, 2020"] {{Wayback|url=https://boardgamegeek.com/thread/2352850 |date=20210417032200 }}. BoardGameGeek.com.  Retrieved 31 January 2020.</ref>。

自2006年以来，该网站每年都会颁发年度最佳棋类新游金极客奖（Golden Geek Award），胜者根据注册用户投票选出<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/2/13/8034777/the-best-tabletop-rpgs-of-2014-finalists-from-board-game-geek |title=The best tabletop RPGs of 2014, finalists from Board Game Geek |last=Hall |first=Charlie |date=2015-02-13 |website=Polygon |access-date=2016-11-10 |archive-date=2019-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190526142050/https://www.polygon.com/2015/2/13/8034777/the-best-tabletop-rpgs-of-2014-finalists-from-board-game-geek |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

自2005年以来，BoardGameGeek每年举办一次棋盘游戏大会（BGG.CON），大会重点聚焦于游戏和金极客奖的公布。会上还会进行新游戏展示及培训大会员工讲授规则<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.escapistmagazine.com/articles/view/tabletop/15131-13-New-Tabletop-Games-for-Winter-The-Best-of-BGG-Con-2015 |title=13 New Tabletop Games for Winter - The Best of BGG Con |last=Morgan |first=Matt |newspaper=The Escapist |access-date=2016-11-25 |archive-date=2018-11-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116030903/https://www.escapistmagazine.com/articles/view/tabletop/15131-13-New-Tabletop-Games-for-Winter-The-Best-of-BGG-Con-2015 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。每年春天也会举办面向家庭的Spring BGG.CON以及一年一度的BGG@Sea巡游。

2010年，BoardGameGeek获得了{{tsl|en|Diana Jones Award|戴安娜·琼斯奖}}，该奖项认可BoardGameGeek是“棋牌界的不二资源，是该在线社区公认的权威。”<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dianajonesaward.org/the-2010-award/ |title=The 2010 Award for Excellence in Gaming |website=The Diana Jones Award |access-date=2016-11-10 |archive-date=2021-03-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309054244/https://www.dianajonesaward.org/the-2010-award/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》称BoardGameGeek为“互联网棋盘游戏的中心”<ref name="nyt-draper-2019">{{cite web |last1=Draper |first1=Kevin |title=Should Board Gamers Play the Roles of Racists, Slavers and Nazis? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/01/style/board-games-cancel-culture.html |publisher=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |access-date=2019-08-02 |date=2019-08-01 |archive-date=2021-02-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224225134/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/01/style/board-games-cancel-culture.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

BoardGameGeek通过使用相同的RPG和电子游戏系统已扩展到其他领域（rpggeek.com及videogamegeek.com）。

